    "summary": "Operations executive with 25+ experience in Manufacturing, Continuous Improvement, Operational Excellence, Change Management and Supply Chain in global B2B environments of specialty- and commodity products. Served as managing director for principal companies within SABIC reporting to supervisory boards.\n\nPractices a hands on, people focused, inclusive and inspiring style to engage people around shared objectives and make them go the extra mile. Applies strong communication to build bridges with key stakeholders at all levels of the organization. Demonstrates conceptual thinking and an analytical approach in order to break down and simplify complex issues to drive continuous improvement.\n\nHas a proven track record in running and improving large single and multi-site operations in complex international corporate environments: improves safety, delivers results on key performance areas, drives operational excellence and manages change well. Strong cross cultural awareness. Builds and drives strong interaction with business teams to support business objectives by operational initiatives. Commissioned and decommissioned chemical plants.\n\nStrong expertise of operational excellence management systems: work processes, organization models, work culture transformation, KPI management, personal- and process safety frameworks, asset performance management and Lean Six Sigma improvement techniques. Proven experience with talent development, performance appraisal and - differentiation processes and managing labor relations with works council and unions, also during re-organizations. Led global change management project. Understanding of different supply chain models. \n\nManufacturing | Operations | Supply Chain | Tangible results | Operational Excellence | Project Management | Change Management | People Management | Performance Management | Labor relations | Continuous Improvement | Lean Six Sigma | Master Black Belt | COO | Executive | General Manager | VP 